---
import '../styles/global.css';
const lastUpdated = '16 April 2026';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Terms & Conditions — Aethelgard</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Terms and conditions for Aethelgard software." />
  <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
</head>
<body class="bg-white text-neutral-900 font-sans antialiased">

  <nav class="sticky top-0 z-50 bg-navy-900 border-b border-white/5">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 h-14 flex items-center justify-between">
      <a href="/" class="text-white font-black tracking-tight text-lg">Aethelgard</a>
      <a href="/" class="text-sm font-semibold text-white/60 hover:text-white transition-colors">← Home</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <header class="bg-navy-900 py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-black tracking-tighter text-white mb-4">Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>
      <p class="text-white/50 text-sm">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <div class="space-y-10 text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black tracking-tight text-neutral-900 mb-4">1. Agreement</h2>
        <p>Aethelgard is a product of <strong>2B Connected Ltd</strong>, a private limited company registered in England and Wales (Company No. 06427186) ("we", "us", "our").</p>
        <p class="mt-3">By downloading, installing, or using Aethelgard ("the Software"), you agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions. If you do not agree, do not use the Software.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black tracking-tight text-neutral-900 mb-4">2. License grant</h2>
        <p>Subject to your purchase of a valid license and compliance with these Terms, we grant you a non-exclusive, non-transferable, personal license to install and use the Software on devices you own or control.</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-3 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Annual license:</strong> Valid for 12 months from the date of purchase. Renews annually if you purchase a new license.</li>
          <li><strong>Lifetime license:</strong> Valid in perpetuity with no further payments required.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4">Your license key is personal to you and may not be shared, sold, or transferred to another person or organisation.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black tracking-tight text-neutral-900 mb-4">3. Permitted use</h2>
        <p>You may use the Software for personal and professional financial record-keeping. You may install the Software on multiple devices that you personally own and control under a single license.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black tracking-tight text-neutral-900 mb-4">4. Restrictions</h2>
        <p>You may not:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-3 space-y-2">
          <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble the Software</li>
          <li>Redistribute, sublicense, rent, or lend the Software to third parties</li>
          <li>Use the Software to provide services to third parties on a commercial bureau basis</li>
          <li>Remove or alter any copyright notices or license validation mechanisms</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black tracking-tight text-neutral-900 mb-4">5. Trial period</h2>
        <p>The Software includes a 30-day free trial providing full Corporate-tier access from the date of first installation, with no credit card required. After the trial period, the Software reverts to Personal-tier functionality unless a license is activated.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black tracking-tight text-neutral-900 mb-4">6. Updates</h2>
        <p>We may release updates, bug fixes, and new features from time to time. Updates are provided at our discretion. We do not guarantee any specific update schedule or the addition of specific features.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black tracking-tight text-neutral-900 mb-4">7. Your data</h2>
        <p>The Software stores all data locally on your device. You are solely responsible for maintaining backups of your data. We are not liable for any data loss resulting from hardware failure, software error, or any other cause.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black tracking-tight text-neutral-900 mb-4">8. No financial advice</h2>
        <p>Aethelgard is a record-keeping and financial management tool. Nothing in the Software or on this website constitutes financial, investment, tax, or legal advice. You are responsible for ensuring that your use of the Software and any decisions made based on information within it comply with applicable laws and regulations.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black tracking-tight text-neutral-900 mb-4">9. Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
        <p>The Software is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind, express or implied. We do not warrant that the Software will be error-free, uninterrupted, or fit for any particular purpose. To the fullest extent permitted by applicable law, we disclaim all warranties.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black tracking-tight text-neutral-900 mb-4">10. Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p>To the fullest extent permitted by applicable law, our total liability to you for any claim arising from your use of the Software shall not exceed the amount you paid for your current license. We shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black tracking-tight text-neutral-900 mb-4">11. Termination</h2>
        <p>We may terminate your license immediately if you breach these Terms. Upon termination, you must cease all use of the Software. Termination does not entitle you to a refund except as provided in our Refund Policy.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black tracking-tight text-neutral-900 mb-4">12. Governing law</h2>
        <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales. Any disputes shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black tracking-tight text-neutral-900 mb-4">13. Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions about these Terms: <a href="mailto:contact@aethelgard.finance" class="text-brand-600 hover:text-brand-700 font-medium">contact@aethelgard.finance</a></p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          <strong>2B Connected Ltd</strong><br />
          Registered in England &amp; Wales · Company No. 06427186
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <footer class="bg-navy-900 py-8 px-6 mt-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-4 text-white/30 text-xs">
      <div class="space-y-1 text-center sm:text-left">
        <span>© {new Date().getFullYear()} Aethelgard. All rights reserved.</span>
        <p class="text-white/20">2B Connected Ltd · Registered in England &amp; Wales · Company No. 06427186</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-6">
        <a href="/privacy" class="hover:text-white/60 transition-colors">Privacy</a>
        <a href="/terms" class="text-white/60">Terms</a>
        <a href="/refunds" class="hover:text-white/60 transition-colors">Refunds</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>

</body>
</html>
